{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"1492","heading":"Authority to provide travel and transportation allowances in connection with transfer ceremonies of certain civilian employees who die overseas","label":"1492 Authority to provide travel and transportation allowances in connection with transfer ceremonies of certain civilian employees who die overseas","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s1492","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/stA/ptII/ch75/schII","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs1492","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","References in Text, referred to in subsec. (a), was repealed by , , .Section 481f of title 37Pub. L. 117–81, div. A, title VI, § 604(a)135 Stat. 1767Dec. 27, 2021"],"amendments":["References in Text, referred to in subsec. (a), was repealed by , , .Section 481f of title 37Pub. L. 117–81, div. A, title VI, § 604(a)135 Stat. 1767Dec. 27, 2021"],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":".—Authority","label":"a .—Authority","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s1492/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s1492","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs1492%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"A covered official may treat a covered relative of a covered employee under the jurisdiction of that covered official in the same manner the Secretary of a military department treats, under section 481f(d) of title 37, next of kin and family members of a member of the armed forces who dies while located or serving overseas.1See References in Text note below.1","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":".—Definitions","label":"b .—Definitions","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s1492/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s1492","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs1492%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-1